The value of $$\left| {\matrix{
   {(a + 1)(a + 2)} &amp; {a + 2} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {(a + 2)(a + 3)} &amp; {a + 3} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {(a + 3)(a + 4)} &amp; {a + 4} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right|$$ is :

questions.solution:
Given, $$\Delta $$ = $$\left| {\matrix{
   {(a + 1)(a + 2)} &amp; {a + 2} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {(a + 2)(a + 3)} &amp; {a + 3} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {(a + 3)(a + 4)} &amp; {a + 4} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right|$$
<br><br>R<sub>2</sub> $$ \to $$ R<sub>2</sub> $$-$$ R<sub>1</sub> and R<sub>3</sub> $$ \to $$ R<sub>3</sub> $$-$$ R<sub>1</sub><br><br>$$\Delta$$ = $$\left| {\matrix{
   {(a + 1)(a + 2)} &amp; {a + 2} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {(a + 2)(a + 3 - a - 1)} &amp; 1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {{a^2} + 7a + 12 - {a^2} - 3a - 2} &amp; 2 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = \left| {\matrix{
   {{a^2} + 3a + 2} &amp; {a + 2} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {2(a + 2)} &amp; 1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {4a + 10} &amp; 2 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = 4(a + 2) - 4a - 10$$<br><br>$$ = 4a + 8 - 4a - 10 =  - 2$$

