   6 &amp; { - 3} &amp; 3  \cr 
   { - 5} &amp; 3 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$ and $$2A - B = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 5  \cr 
   2 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 6  \cr 
   0 &amp; 1 &amp; 2  \cr 

 } } \right]$$. If Tr(A) denotes the sum of all diagonal elements of the matrix A, then Tr(A) $$-$$ Tr(B) has value equal to

